🌸🕉22nd Jan 2022🕉🌸

The day we tie the knot and celebrate our love.❤️🥂
There’s barely any time left!!
.
With everything that’s currently happening, it’s going to be an intimate wedding with just our immediate families.
We know we have everyone’s love and blessings and that’s all we need for now.🙏🏻
.
It’s been crazy last few weeks planning the wedding for 200 people to begin with and then downsizing everything to 20 & re-starting from scratch. But then, from trousseau shopping together to sharing Pinterest boards for decor ideas or even taking a parantha break at Chandni Chowk, finalizing the mangalsutra design to picking the chooda together, or picking the safa & kalgi that goes with the sherwani or food tasting sessions with caterers … every small thing to anything big we’ve enjoyed every bit of this process no matter how hectic it got! Can’t wait to see how it all comes out & just get married!!🥂❤️

latestIgtvVideos.title: Easy Festive Look GRWM!✨
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
.
.
With the festive season here, we all have the perfect excuse to finally play dress up and cheer up in this pandemic situation at hand. I am quite excited that I can finally put on some nice clothes, play with makeup and meet my family and friends.
While of course, with the masks on it’s tough to do much with the makeup which is why I am mostly focusing on eyes now when it comes to it.
To make sure my eyes get all the attention I start with my @bauschandlombindia @lacelle_in coloured lenses. They have a great range of colours and are super comfortable to wear! I personally like the fact how natural it still looks!
I kept this looks easy to do & nothing OTT so everyone can pull it off without thinking too much about it.
Here’s the makeup break up:
1) Lacelle Diamond Daily Lenses shade D-Aqua (you can always consult your eye care professional for more information) 
2) @esteelauderin the mattifier primer 
3) @chanel.beauty le tient ultra foundation shade 40
4) @sephora_india concealer shade 30 
5) @lauramercier setting powder, good enough of it so the makeup lasts under the mask too 
6) @benefitindia goof proof brow pencil shade 4.5
7) @toofaced pretty rich eye shadow palette 
8) @toofaced better than sex mascara 
9) @tartecosmetics clay blush palette 
10) @toofaced canary diamond highlighter 
11) @smashboxindia babe alert liquid lipstic, rubbing it with finger gives it a more tint feel and it doesn’t smudge under the mask as well.
And that’s it, quick, easy and wearable for small festivities and occasions if you don’t wanna go full glam!🌸✨
.
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: BEING COVID-19 POSITIVE!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
.
.
Sharing my experience and all that I had to go through being #Covid19 positive myself.🦠 
It’s a long video since I tried to include everything I could possibly. From my symptoms to how I managed, the health department bit and the do’s & dont’s for people who’ve tested positive and people around them. 
Please feel free to ask me any question based on my experience that I have shared here or something I missed out on. 
I made the video purely with the intent of sharing my personal experience as #covidpositive & opinions on a few things around it. This is no way an educational video & neither am I trying to ‘consult’ anyone medically or share any expert opinions. The idea is to help people in any way I can based on how I dealt with it.
🌺 My parents & my family/siblings were obviously super stressed when they got to know. I think it was emotionally taxing for my parents to have their sick child away, but I wouldn’t have it any other way! I am glad I wasn’t with them during all this, no way I would have risked infecting my family. I was in constant touch with my mom dad, sending them pics of oximeter & thermometer reading or even Kaada pics and what not. I wanted them to stay calm. I know they know that they raised their daughter strong, but you know, it was pretty emotional for them. Love you mom dad!❤️🌺
Please feel free to share this video if you think it can help anyone. 
I am officially covid negative now, though still practicing strict home isolation till 29th (the date allotted to me by the health dept.). I will continue to take all necessary precautions even after that. 
Take care!❤️
.
UPDATE: I went to nearest plasma bank to donate plasma post recovery, as a voluntary donor but was denied as I have PCOS. Apparently you can’t donate plasma is you have pcos.
.
Also, I think I have had enough share of the negativity around it too as a covid patient so I will just block anyone who tries to hate on me for the same. Not because it affects me or anything but only because I am not going to entertain any bullshit here, zero space for negativity.✌🏻
.
#corona #coronavirus #pandemic #covid19positive #covid_19 #covidpatient #beingcovid19positive #Mycovidjourney

latestIgtvVideos.title: Domestic Violence & COVID-19
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I have been wanting to start a conversation on #DomesticViolence & #FamilyAbuse more seriously on my page for a really long time. I have already been sharing bits of it in my stories for a while now but I guess it was about time to get more serious about the topic since the cases are on the rise with the #Lockdown #Covid19 and no matter how many cases seem to be reported, we know it’s all a tip of the iceberg. 
Trying to discuss the challenges here in the video as to why the cases are on a rise and why a lot of people still don’t report it. Let’s discuss! What is our government doing, what more it can do? Further, how can we reach out to more and more people who need help? We need to make noise loud enough to reach the authorities so the issue is taken up more seriously. Tell me what do you think? How do we bring #PeaceAtHome 🙏🏻
I mean, the lockdown keeps extending and that’s definitely not helping anyone and it does worries me, how many more people must be going through #DomesticAbuse who aren’t even able to seek any help because of #Corona #SocialDistancing let’s talk!! Now!
.
Big thank you to everyone who’s been part of this video directly or indirectly. Let’s make some noise! @tamseel_h @pluctv @pluc.in  @sharmavrekha @ncwindia @thesafespace.in @volunteers.collective @about.tanvi 
There are more videos and posts coming up to get more into this issue!
.
Disclaimer: kindly ignore my pace here, I get emotional about this topic and my head’s not focussing on my talking pace, and that’s how I usually talk but I’ll keep it in mind for future videos. Let’s focus on the message here.🌸
